body_html:
1. uninstalling tensorflow
  2. install master
  3. Check whether you are able to import tensorflow --> If it works first,
    then upgrade to 0.7

Already done that according to the previous recommandations and it doesn't work.

You may want to check the python path and verify the version on protocol
buffer during your installation.

My PYTHONPATH variable is perfectly set because all the modules are recognized (including "protobuf") but not "google.protobuf". The version of the installed "Protobuf" is "3.0.0b2" which seems to be the good one.
